Tri-Sprintec is dispensed in a blister pack tablet dispenser [see HOW SUPPLIED]. Tri-Sprintec may be started using either a Day 1 start or a Sunday start (see Table 1). For the first cycle of a Sunday Start regimen, an additional method of contraception should be used until after the first 7 consecutive days of administration.
Table 1: Instructions for Administration of Tri-Sprintec 
First-trimester
Second-trimester
There are two ways to start taking birth control pills, Sunday Start or Day 1 Start. Your healthcare professional will tell you which to use.

Three Ways To Remember In What Order To Take The Pills
Table 2: Instructions for Missed Tri-Sprintec Tablets 
In case of severe vomiting or diarrhea, absorption may not be complete and additional contraceptive measures should be taken. If vomiting or diarrhea occurs within 3 to 4 hours after taking an active tablet, handle this as a missed tablet [see FDA-ApprovedPatient Labeling].
The timing of initiation of dosing with Tri-Sprintec for acne should follow the guidelines for use of Tri-Sprintec as an oral contraceptive. Consult the DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION section (2.1) for instructions.
